On the racism, race realism, IQ, selective immigration stuff here, the basic point is: If racial inequality of outcomes is considered intolerable (as it was to the pre-Glorious Revolution II regime), then you are set on a policy path that will destroy everything that works, and still not resolve the problem you're aiming to eliminate. In the end you're going to have to absolutely relax about disparate impact, domestically and internationally, or die. x.com/BMStudebaker/status/19â€¦

... My implicit argument with Mikey is that he sees 'race realism' as a positive metaphysical commitment (to biological essences, or something) where I see only the abandonment of an untenable metaphysical commitment (to natural equality justly expressed through similarity of outcomes).

Humanism doesn't do any useful work. 
Liberal formal equality of agents works for anonymous accounts of all kinds (also for AIs). You get it for free, so no need for ideological justification. 
Homo Sapiens as a biological category is useful when people are being honest about it, under increasingly precarious scientific conditions (sensitive to admixture, and sub-species). 
'Man' as something to care about indiscriminately leads into terrible policy pathways.
This post is getting a lot of criticism, but I think it's true that contemporary white people are (in general) uniquely dishonest, due primarily to the moralistic fallacy.
